article.description: Danielle McCray scored 20 points and Kansas (No. 19 AP) used a late 11-0 run to beat Iowa 66-55 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: McCray scores 20 as Jayhawks slip by Hawkeyes
article.linkText: McCray, Kansas use late run to thwart Iowa
article.story:
IOWA CITY, Iowa -- Danielle McCray scored 20 points and Kansas (No. 19 AP) used a late 11-0 run to beat Iowa 66-55 on Wednesday night.

McCray missed nine of her first 10 shots and had only five points at the break. However, the 5-foot-11 senior made several key baskets in the second half for the Jayhawks (2-0).

All five Kansas starters scored in double figures with Aishah Sutherland finishing with 12 points, Krysten Boogaard 11, Sade Morris 10 and Angel Goodrich 10.

Kachine Alexander had 23 points and 17 rebounds to lead Iowa (2-1).

Trailing 54-51 with 7 minutes to go, Kansas scored 11 straights to gain control. McCray, who led the Big 12 Conference in scoring last season, hit a big 3-pointer during the run to put the Jayhawks up four. Goodrich followed with a pair of buckets.
